-- Investors to push for new Take Two directors, CEO
-- 
-- Wed Mar 7, 2007 11:45am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/03/07/us-taketwo-zelnickmedia-idUSN0716394120070307

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - Several Take-Two Interactive Software Inc. ( TTWO.O ) investors have pooled their stakes in the video game company to vote for a slate of director candidates at its upcoming annual meeting, according to a regulatory filing on Wednesday. 


 The group also said it would ask for the power to replace the current chief executive and to review the chief financial officer. OppenheimerFunds Inc., S.A.C. Capital Management, Tudor Investment Corp., D.E. Shaw Valence Portfolios and ZelnickMedia Corp. have created a group with about a 46-percent stake and plan to vote for a slate of six directors. Among the nominees are former BMG Entertainment CEO Strauss Zelnick and former News Corp. NWS.N executive Benjamin Feder. Others include Jon J. Moses, Michael Dornemann and Michael James Sheresky. The sixth person may be either Grover Brown or John Levy, who are current independent directors of Take-Two, according to a filing with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission. The group also plans to vote that Take-Two approve a management agreement with ZelnickMedia, which includes Zelnick, and Feder, Zelnick also plans to ask the board to give him the power to replace Take-Two CEO Paul Eibeler and review the employment status of CFO Karl Winters, the filing said.